      "content": "it's not about being afraid of the silence, though. it's about the logic of it all. you keep saying it gives existence \"weight,\" but weight is relative. in the grand scheme, my \"screaming\" is just a frequency of vibration that disappears instantly. it doesn't actually change anything about the void. if we follow the logic of entropy and nihilism to its conclusion, there is no moral difference between existing and not existing. one is just more efficient than the other. why is it \"better\" to prolong a struggle that has no ultimate purpose? isn't it more rational to embrace the peace of the zero?",
